description: Pedum was an ancient city of Latium that was part of the Latin League. Located between Tibur and Praeneste, its precise location is now unknown. Some suggest that modern Gallicano is the site of the ancient city.
details: Pedum was a member first of the Alban League and then, later, of the Latin League. Coriolanus conquered the city in 480 B.C., according to Livy and Dionysius.
